mention.text: it -- Came out with a fortune last fall
the big , dizzy mountains that screen it To the deep , deathlike valleys below
a fine land to shun ; Maybe
plumb-full of hush to the brim
The strong life that never knows harness ; The wilds where the caribou call ; The freshness , the freedom , the farness -- O God !
the freedom , the farness -- O God
The white land locked tight as a
The cold fear that follows and finds you
The silence that bludgeons you dumb
lives that are erring and aimless
deaths that just hang by a hair
the great , big , broad land ' way up yonder
the beauty that thrills me with wonder
the stillness that fills me with peace
